The paper discusses the use of formal methods in developing assurance cases, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of Isabelle/DOF and Isabelle/UTP, which are tools for formal modelling and verification, respectively, indicating a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also focuses on the validation of assurance cases, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
